Murder most foul: Soldier was ordered to support his 2 children             Jacinta Mutura  18th Nov 2019 02:00:00 GMT +0300 Jacinta Mutura  18th Nov 2019 02:00:00 GMT +0300 Jacinta Mutura   Ms Joyce Maua, 31, who went missing on October 26, 2019 together with her two children Shanice (10) and Prince Michael (5) after visiting a senior military officer based at Laikipia Air Base. The officer identified as Major Peter Mugure is said to be the father of the two children and they had visited at his request after schools closed. [Philip Muasya, Standard]  Ms Joyce Maua, 31, who went missing on October 26, 2019 together with her two children Shanice (10) and Prince Michael (5) after visiting a senior military officer based at Laikipia Air Base. The officer identified as Major Peter Mugure is said to be the father of the two children and they had visited at his request after schools closed. [Philip Muasya, Standard] Ms Joyce Maua, 31, who went missing on October 26, 2019 together with her two children Shanice (10) and Prince Michael (5) after visiting a senior military officer based at Laikipia Air Base. The officer identified as Major Peter Mugure is said to be the father of the two children and they had visited at his request after schools closed. [Philip Muasya, Standard] Ms Joyce Maua, 31, who went missing on October 26, 2019 together with her two children Shanice (10) and Prince Michael (5) after visiting a senior military officer based at Laikipia Air Base. The officer identified as Major Peter Mugure is said to be the father of the two children and they had visited at his request after schools closed. soldier who is being held by police in connection with the murder of his estranged lover and two children            The Standard  For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.       Close relationship Close relationship           The Standard   Domestic issue